How do you respond to criticism
I see criticism as an opportunity to improve. When I receive feedback, I make sure to listen carefully and understand the specific points being raised. I also appreciate the person taking the time to share it, so I usually thank them for their input.
Then, I reflect on the feedback and identify what I can do better. I try not to take it personally, but instead focus on how it helps me grow. If needed, I may ask follow-up questions to clarify expectations and ensure I improve effectively. Overall, I see feedback as an important part of my development.
